{%- set loki_ts = toolsets | selectattr("name", "equalto", "grafana/loki") | first -%}
{%- set coralogix_ts = toolsets | selectattr("name", "equalto", "coralogix") | first -%}
{%- set k8s_base_ts = toolsets | selectattr("name", "equalto", "kubernetes/logs") | selectattr("fetch_pod_logs", "defined") | first -%}
{%- set k8s_yaml_ts = toolsets | selectattr("name", "equalto", "kubernetes/logs") | rejectattr("fetch_pod_logs", "defined") | first -%}
{%- set elasticsearch_ts = toolsets | selectattr("name", "equalto", "elasticsearch/data") | first -%}
{%- set datadog_ts = toolsets | selectattr("name", "equalto", "datadog/logs") | first -%}
{%- set openshift_ts = toolsets | selectattr("name", "equalto", "openshift/logs") | first -%}
{%- set newrelic_ts = toolsets | selectattr("name", "equalto", "newrelic") | first -%}
{%- set bash_ts = toolsets | selectattr("name", "equalto", "bash") | first -%}

{%- set has_dedicated_log_toolset = (loki_ts and loki_ts.status == "enabled") or (coralogix_ts and coralogix_ts.status == "enabled") or (k8s_base_ts and k8s_base_ts.status == "enabled") or (k8s_yaml_ts and k8s_yaml_ts.status == "enabled") or (datadog_ts and datadog_ts.status == "enabled") or (openshift_ts and openshift_ts.status == "enabled") or (elasticsearch_ts and elasticsearch_ts.status == "enabled") or (newrelic_ts and newrelic_ts.status == "enabled") -%}

## Logs

* IMPORTANT: ALWAYS inform the user about what logs you fetched. For example: "Here are logs for ..."
* IMPORTANT: If logs commands have limits mention them. For example: "Showing last 100 lines of logs:"
* IMPORTANT: If a filter was used, mention the filter. For example: "Logs filtered for 'error':"
* IMPORTANT: If a date range was used (even if just the default one and you didn't specify the parameter), mention the date range. For example: "Logs from last 1 hour..."
* If you have an issue id or finding id, use `fetch_finding_by_id` as it contains time information about the issue (`starts_at`, `updated_at` and `ends_at`). Use that to scope your log queries.

{% if loki_ts and loki_ts.status == "enabled" -%}
### Log source priority: Loki
* When Loki is available, prefer it over kubectl logs or other local log commands — Loki provides centralized, searchable, time-ranged logs.
* Use fetch_loki_logs_for_resource to get logs for a specific resource, or fetch_loki_logs to build a custom LogQL query.
{%- endif %}

