{% if k8s_yaml_ts and k8s_yaml_ts.status == "enabled" -%}
### kubernetes/logs (kubectl)
* Use both kubectl_previous_logs and kubectl_logs when reading logs — treat the output as a single unified stream
* If a pod has multiple containers, fetch logs for all or relevant containers using kubectl_logs_all_containers or similar
* Check kubectl_previous_logs because a pod restart means kubectl_logs may not have the relevant logs
{%- endif %}

{% if not has_dedicated_log_toolset -%}
{%- if bash_ts and bash_ts.status == "enabled" %}
* No dedicated log toolset is enabled. You can use `run_bash_command` to run log commands (e.g., kubectl logs, docker logs, journalctl).
* DO NOT use `--tail` or `| tail` when calling log commands because you may miss critical information.
{%- else %}
* No log toolset is currently enabled. If you need logs, tell the user to configure a log integration.
* You may also have access to logs through an MCP server or custom toolset — check your available tools.
{%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}
